From Brad Templeton Subject Re text of White House announcement and Q As on clipper chip encryption The stragegy of the government is The real fear comes from them doing more than This is a voluntary program and thus harder for us to object to on the Their strategy is a business one rather than legal They are pushing to get a standard in place a secret standard and if they get it as a standard then they will drive competitors out of the It will be legal to sell better untapable encryption that doesn't have registered keys but it will be difficult and thus not a plan for most phone You see with clipper chip phones you'll be able to talk to any cellular company or other phones or ports because they will follow the AT T has already announced a clipper chip encryption The government has marketed hard to get major vendors to use these If they get enough market share they will And thus there will be very little market for systems that can't be tapped by the The public isn't that concerned about it now after They freely do calls that anybody with an old TV can listen to today They won't pay big extra bucks for proprietary phones that secure them only from the Well some people will buy these phones but they will only work with other proprietary phones so the market will be small and the phones Unless they are made in numbers large enough to sell them cheap only the Mob will buy And this means that the FBI will want to track the customer lists of better encryption phones because the only reason a person would want one is to evade the Brad Templeton ClariNet Communications Sunnyvale CA